##Shortage of transport capacity, insufficient masks, the safety of the delivery guy who will guard?

Weixin Signal Wowjiemian

Function introduction, the interface news is China has the influence original financial and economic new media, only serves the independent thinking crowd

Image: Tubo

Reporter: Zhou Yixue, editor Yang Xia: Wen Shuqi

“

Nationwide Mobility was suspended, and industries such as takeout and express delivery, which rely on offline capacity, were affected.

”

“

Nationwide Mobility was suspended, and industries such as takeout and express delivery, which rely on offline capacity, were affected.

”

Shortly after 12 pm, Zhang Li, who was shopping for the next day, was forced to find that a dozen pre delivery slots at 7Fresh had been fully booked, and another shopping platform, Youxian daily, had been closed, is Temporarily off-line within two hours of the performance of the speed up service, only three days of delivery of fresh supermarket choice.

Affected by the outbreak, Zhang Li has reduced the frequency of travel, daily food requirements are almost online purchase. Zhang Li is in good company, and with the outbreak, orders on every major fresh e commerce platform have seen a surge.

For the major fresh e-commerce, this would have been a good time to expand business quickly. After actively adjusting the supply chain to ensure an adequate supply of goods, platforms are finding that shortages of manpower and capacity are the new bottlenecks.

Not only fresh e-commerce, the Spring Festival after the gradual resumption of normal business in the express delivery industry also stuck in the same bottleneck.

According to the State Post Bureau, there are more than 3 million front line couriers in the country. According to the Meituan report, in 2018, more than 2.7 million riders in the Meituan Platform Income. Nearly 70 percent of the nearly 6 million couriers and deliverymen are from rural areas. To prevent the spread of the epidemic, local governments have introduced some measures to control the flow of people. This has led to the return of Chinese New Year couriers, deliverymen, etc. temporarily unable to return to work.

###Supplies of masks vary

After most of the country's residential areas were closed to traffic, the most common residents were thought to be couriers and delivery men. At the same time, whether the courier have enough masks, whether to do a good job of self-protection measures, has also become a problem of concern to residents.

At crowded stations, couriers wear face masks and try to minimize verbal communication with each other. But masks are still a scarce commodity, and whether each courier has enough depends on the availability of the person in charge of his site.

The owner of a county-level branch of zto express in Sichuan told interface news that they have been back to work since February 9. There are 11 couriers returning from the site, plus clerks and operators, making a total of 14 employees.

At present, the reserve of more than 400 ordinary masks, a day to the staff, before work to the staff to check their temperature, work to use disinfection water. The local postal administration uniformly purchased two large buckets of disinfectant water, each about 50 Jin, which is expected to be used for one month.

But if the 400 masks run out, the boss is also worried about where to shop, "The county pharmacy has run out of masks. I asked some personal sellers who sell masks. N95 costs 25 yuan each. I can't afford it. Now the rest of the mask is to ask a friend to buy, the price is more expensive, each 3 yuan. According to my friend, I think the price of the mask will go up."

The head of the Hubei Branch of a courier company said the company organized the purchase of two batches of epidemic prevention materials, including medical masks, N95 masks, disinfectant (tablets) , goggles, protective clothing and medical gloves. The company did not officially resume work after the shutdown in Wuhan, but some employees were on duty and were involved in the transportation of first-line relief supplies.

Its Wuhan Distribution Center, for example, usually has 500-600 employees, the current staff of about 30 people, including managers, sorting workers, Stevedores and transport drivers.

In the protection measures, for all employees, the company in their daily access to the operation site to take temperature, registration work; for the General Indoor Work of the staff on duty, each day issued a General Medical Mask; Additional N95 masks, goggles, protective clothing and gloves are issued to drivers who deliver supplies to the front line.

At present, in its reserves of anti-epidemic, killing materials, ordinary masks remaining more than 10,000, according to the level of each employee a day, short-term enough for duty staff. But the reserves will not be enough if work resumes at full capacity.

"If we do go back to work in full, the daily consumption will be huge, " the official told interface news. "We have to make purchases according to the situation. Some of US have to seek help from headquarters, and some of US have to figure it out on our own. "

Even if the company provides protective materials such as masks, front-line couriers and delivery agents face a more complicated situation as they travel long distances every day to reach large numbers of residents.

Wang Feng, a courier from Hebei, told interface news that he now gets two masks a week from his company, and to save money, he washes them with disinfectant every night and uses them repeatedly.

Chen, a delivery man at Shaoxing Point Wada logistics in Danniao, had a much worse experience when he was evicted by his landlord after registering with the community.

"The landlord said it was because I was delivering express and take-out food, which was unsafe and too sensitive, " Chen said. "The rent contract hasn't expired yet, but there's no way. " He plans to wait for other colleagues to return to work, and once there is no shortage of riders at the station, so I went back to my hometown and changed my job from being a jockey.

###General capacity shortage

Wang Feng's express delivery station is located in Pingleyuan, Chaoyang District, Beijing. Under normal circumstances, this station delivers more than 3,000 express delivery orders every day. At full capacity, there are more than 20 couriers. Now, due to the impact of the epidemic, there's a partial capacity gap.

A total of seven couriers from the site returned home for the Lunar New Year holiday, and five still have not returned to Beijing, Wang Feng told interface news. "It's hard to say when they will return to Beijing, because many places are now closed to road closures. "

There is a capacity gap, and people have been shopping online more than ever during the outbreak. Wang Feng's workload was heavier than usual. Now he delivers more than 200 delivery orders a day, 50 more than usual. The working hours start at 6 am and continue after 8 pm.

"There's a lot of pressure to get a bill, " Wang Feng said. "I'm afraid of getting infected, too, but since I'm doing this job, I'm trying to be careful. "

Capacity gap not only exists in the express industry, each fresh e-commerce platform and take-away platform is the same.

During the outbreak, fresh e-commerce providers of basic commodities such as vegetables, fruits, meat and eggs received a wave of orders. According to daily Youxian CFO Wang Jun, daily Youxian platform transactions during the epidemic period more than tripled. Meituan said recently, Beijing, Shanghai, Shenzhen, Wuhan four areas of sales rose significantly, and showed a continuing upward trend, with the Beijing area of the highest daily sales 2-3 times the pre-festival.

On the one hand is the order quantity of the Meng Zeng, on the other hand is the capacity of the performance difficulties caused by insufficient.

"when the epidemic started, there was a lot of turbulence, because many employees went home for the New Year and the number of units exceeded the historical peak, " Wang said. Wang Fei, vice president of logistics delivery at daily Youxian, said that the biggest problem facing the platform is the lack of staff and that there is general anxiety among employees on the front lines.

Take the Beijing area as an example, the interface news actual measurement found that Meituan shopping, home delivery in JD.com all day, can basically achieve 1 hour up. Box Ma fresh transport capacity tension, often shows that the distribution booking is full, customers need to shop for themselves. Fresh daily Youxian DA has relaxed the statute of limitations from 1 hour to 2 hours, but there are still some areas due to large orders or a shortage of riders, can not guarantee the statute of limitations.

Delivery Platform is faced with a decline in orders and a shortage of capacity double situation. A delivery man at Shilihe station in Chaoyang District, Beijing, told interface news that his delivery station had more than 40 people when it was full, and now there are fewer than 20 because of the epidemic prevention requirements, many of the Chinese New Year's home delivery workers are now unable to return to work.

But the drop in take-out orders in the Beijing area is more pronounced, so overall work is not too busy. "The number of deliveries per day is now down from fifty per day to twenty per day, " the deliveryman said.

###Industry helps industry

In response to shortages of capacity and supplies, several online platforms have teamed up with industries such as restaurants and hotels that have been hard hit by the outbreak, such as co-sourcing food and recruiting idle staff.

Wang Fei predicted that the epidemic as a whole would continue for some time. The next step, he said, is for daily fresh to work more closely with restaurants and other industries to address supply and distribution issues. Now, daily fresh has been with Xibei, Meizhou Dongpo and other catering enterprises, by the Xibei and Meizhou Dongpo to provide warehouse and staff, for the daily fresh Chinese cabbage will be processed into standard dishes. In north China, the two companies provide Youxian with 100,000 items a day.

In the transport capacity, daily fresh and excellent is actively in the delivery platform to carry out cooperation. "Now a lot of catering companies can not start work, take-out platform single volume is very small, these take-out capacity can also cooperate with us to link the pressure of delivery, related cooperation is in the talks, " Wang Fei said. In addition, in order to cope with the lack of capacity, improve the efficiency of performance, to ensure the delivery of time, every excellent fresh also added tricycle as a distribution tool to increase the capacity of a single trip.

On Feb. 7, ele.me launched Blue Ocean, a job-sharing platform, inviting 100,000 restaurants to recruit 10,000 temporary riders. Ele.me said that the sharing platform will also connect 200,000 stores, convenience stores, catering staff can be engaged in take-away order sorting, handling and other urgently needed positions.

On February 8th JD.COM and its investment arm, Datta, announced that it would employ more than 35,000 people across the country in a variety of ways.

JD.com logistics will open more than 20,000 first-line jobs nationwide, including storekeepers, sorters, couriers and drivers. Dada Group's Dada Express platform will be more than 2400 counties and cities across the country to recruit knights, the first batch to recruit 10,000 knights; Dada Group's jd.com platform will assist retail partners in recruiting pickers, packers and other store positions in more than 30 cities across the country, opening up more than 5,000 positions.

Jd.com said that JD.com logistics will provide new employees with comprehensive pre-job training in operation and protection standards, and provide emergency supplies such as face masks, thermometers and disinfectants in accordance with the requirements of the National Epidemic Prevention and control, do a good job of temperature testing, disinfection and other preventive and control measures.

In addition, various delivery platforms or e-commerce platforms said that they have equipped riders or couriers with face masks, disinfectant and other epidemic prevention materials, requiring front-line employees to be equipped with face masks throughout the entire process, and conduct random health checks. Meituan, Jd.com, Youxian daily and other platforms also bought anti-epidemic insurance for frontline staff, so that field staff can work safely.

But it is worth noting that some of the forms of crowdsourcing platform to send a single individual workers did not get the platform's anti-epidemic supplies. A Meituan crowdsourced delivery man told interface news that his mask had been purchased at his own expense, lacked disinfectant and other items, and was not required by the platform to report his temperature and health status.

Strictly speaking, crowdsourcing employees are not regular employees of the platform, but they provide the same service to consumers, and the absolute number has far exceeded the number of dedicated employees. This part of the population lack of health protection or the current take-out platform epidemic prevention loopholes.
